sentences: Roy James Gaines (August 12, 1937 – August 11, 2021) was an American Texas blues and electric blues guitarist, singer and songwriter.
He wrote and recorded the song "A Hell of a Night", which was first issued on his 1982 album Gainelining.
Gaines was born in Waskom, Texas, and relocated with his family to Houston when he was six years old.
By the age of 14 he had performed onstage backing his hero, T-Bone Walker, and played in Houston nightclubs.
Gaines died on August 11, 2021, a day before his 84th birthday.
